// DeveloperSettings.sample.xcconfig
//
// TEMPLATE — do not fill in this copy. Copy it to a "SharedXcodeSettings"
// folder that sits NEXT TO your OpenAppLock clone (one level above the repo),
// so your personal Team ID lives physically outside git and can never be
// committed by accident:
//
//     Developer/
//     ├── OpenAppLock/                          <- your clone
//     └── SharedXcodeSettings/
//         └── DeveloperSettings.xcconfig        <- copy this file here, then edit
//
// From the repo root:
//
//     mkdir -p ../SharedXcodeSettings
//     cp Config/DeveloperSettings.sample.xcconfig \
//        ../SharedXcodeSettings/DeveloperSettings.xcconfig
//
// Then open the copy and set DEVELOPMENT_TEAM to your 10-character Apple Team
// ID, found at https://developer.apple.com/account → Membership details.
//
// Note: the app and its Screen Time extensions are registered under the
// `dev.bchen.OpenAppLock` bundle-ID prefix and the `group.dev.bchen.OpenAppLock`
// App Group, which belong to the maintainer's team. To run on your own device
// you must also change those identifiers to your own.
// Building and running the tests in the simulator needs no signing at all.

DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = YOUR_TEAM_ID
